marked: Amyloid plaques and neurofibrillary tangles are the pathologic hallmark of Alzheimer disease (AD).

In this present study we sought to examine the correlation between regional brain amyloid plaque load, measured with [11C]PIB-PET, regional cerebral glucose metabolism, measured with [18F]FDGPET, and behavioral performance of subjects with clinically diagnosed AD
